{
  "guid": "lfo ",
  "name": "LFO",
  "description": "This algorithm offers a number of flexible low frequency oscillators.\n\nThe global ‘Quality’ parameter offers two options:\n- ‘Stepped’ quality is extremely low CPU usage, and is appropriate for automating parameters of other algorithms (via mapping).\n- ‘Linear’ quality should be selected if you plan to use the LFOs to output CVs to other modules.\n\nThe LFOs can run freely, or be synced to external clocks or to MIDI clock.\n\nWhen there is more than one LFO channel, channels 2-4 can be locked to the phase of LFO 1. This allows you to create a quadrature LFO. Use the ‘Phase’ parameter of LFOs 2-4 to set the phase relationship in degrees to LFO 1. Note that in this case, the ‘Speed’ and ‘Multiplier’ parameters of the phase-locked LFO have no effect.\n\nThe display shows the shape of the current channel’s output, or if the ‘Globals’ page is active, the shape of all the channels.",
  "categories": [
    "Modulation",
    "Utility",
    "Audio Rate",
    "CV Generation"
  ],
  "short_description": "A low frequency oscillator",
  "use_cases": [
    "Automating parameters via mapping (using 'Stepped' quality)",
    "Generating CV outputs for external modules ('Linear' quality)",
    "Creating complex modulation patterns with phase-locked LFOs",
    "Syncing to MIDI clock or external clocks"
  ],
